originalText.text: If I was able I would give 0 stars. Parked my brand new suv vehicle 7/23 to 7/25. Vehicle had no body damage, when picking up the vehicle the garage attendant could not even locate it for 20 minutes was going back and forth. When picked up the car did not realize to check my roof and gps antenna was scrapped and roof had a huge dent, I only noticed that the next day while pumping gas in the sunlight. The garage forwarded all info for the company that does their claim, "what a surprize" they refuse to approve it because it was not reported right away. Well, when you give a vehicle you don't expect to even check your roof because you expect everyone is going to treat your property with respect and careful behaviour. I have requested their claim company to provide video surveilance recordings showing vehicle arriving and leaving, have not received this info as of yet. I will keep this review here unless the garage managent will step up and own for their garage attendant recless behaviour that damaged my property. Let's see how they want to end this story, the ball is in their hands.

originalText.text: This place is a scam. I use the SpotHero app which shows you the total price you pay for parking. You then pay SpotHero and SpotHero pays the garage. You even enter your vehicle details so there is no confusion on size, etc. Upon arrival at this garage, they told me I’d be paying an additional charge of nearly 100% of the SpotHero price due to being “oversize,” which my car is not. They even put it on an elevator that says “small cars only.” This is a cash grab by them and is effectively theft. Do not use them.

originalText.text: Chaos and Damage!  Friday, September 18th we show up to pick up our car, unfortunately we didn't have our ticket. The female manager recognized me and remembered me dropping the car off, however, she at first refuses to release the car, she finally relented and asked for a drivers license and copy of registration, which we had.  45 minutes later they find the car and bring it up, in this time the garage is chaos with half a dozen people pacing and wanting their cars, 3 people go to the key cabinet and grab their keys, however, the car park attendant left a car at the entrance to the garage and it blocked the exit.  The attendant moves cars and a couple pull out in their deep hunter green Mercedes GLE and promptly hit a black Range Rover, the female manager, saw the whole thing, goes over, inspects both cars, then let's the couple leave, no report, no insurance or note left for the damaged car owner (see photo of damage - its extensive).  Unbelievable!  Everyone who witnessed it was in shock.  We finally demand our car as we were first in line, my husband blocked the manager from moving a car off the elevator, she waves a stick with a key on it and says something about our key and the attendant.  The attendant asks if we provided documents, we say yes as we had with the manager, he's confused and goes to help a Zip-Car renter, we get in our car and drive out with the attendant yelling at us.  So unprofessional, so crazy, we will never go back to this garage and I'm sure we're not wanted, works for us!  Note to the owner of the black Range Rover, we will testify on your behalf if the garage refuses to acknowledge and pay for the damage.  If they try and pull the "we're not responsible, its noted on your ticket" that's BS, they failed to use reasonable care with your car and they are liable.  Be sure to get your car fixed right, no bondo, get the rear panel completely replaced. P.S. Both attendants weren't wearing masks!

DO NOT PARK HERE - ZERO STARS
This garage is not recommended - left the vehicle overnight and when I picked up this morning the drivers seat was all the way back and there was a pillow in there...that is literally appalling.  Do not leave your car here.

originalText.text: Pre paid and made a reservation the day before. I arrived on time and the manager basically was yelling at me that they were full, tried to send me to another garage that was also full when I called. Took no responsibility for taking my money and providing no spot. And refused to refund me.  To the garage owner - please don’t make reservations and take prepayment if you can’t handle it.
